sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1157012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This is constructed through original igem official biobrick.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a biosensor that is built to sense C-4 AHL molecules, and uses luciferase as a reporter. Our advisor has suggested that luciferase acts as a better quantitative measure reporter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This construct lacks functional data due to limited time. We are looking forward for other teams to test this construct and make other appliances.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Lin Ang Chieh

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: rhIR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: rhlR repressor/activator from P. aeruginosa PA3477 (no LVA)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: same as C0071 except no LVA tag
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: jcbraff

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: RhlR+C4
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Promoter activated by RhlR in concert with C4-HSL. C4-HSL is produced by RhlI, and acts as a quorum-sensing autoinducer.

This is the natural sequence taken from Pseudomonas aeruginosa.

Crosstalk: this promoter is also activated at a low level by LasR with its associated HSL.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
The -10 and -35 sites are labeled as identified in [Pearson97].

The part begins with the RhlR binding site, and (rather arbitrarily) ends with the first transcribed base (+1).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Ronny Krashinsky

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0030
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Strong RBS based on Ron Weiss thesis. Strength is considered relative to <bb_part>BBa_B0031</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0032</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0033</bb_part>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix ("orig" in figure 4-14 of Ron Weiss thesis).

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0015
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Double terminator consisting of BBa_B0010 and BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J52008
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: luciferase: luciferin 2-monooxygenase from Renilla reniformis (EC 1.13.12.5; SwissProt:: P27652)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Rluc is a protein called Renilla`s luciferase and it emits light when adding the right substrate. That is why it can bi used as a reported to track other proteins or to monitor the activity of a promotor.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Rluc is cloned in BioBrick vector pSB1AK3.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Monika Ciglic

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg
